1
00:00:16,980 --> 00:00:20,240
Please mind the gap between train and platform

2
00:00:22,980 --> 00:00:25,900
Please mind the gap between train and platform

3
00:00:29,180 --> 00:00:30,760
How old are you?

4
00:00:33,330 --> 00:00:35,330
-If you ask me back, it means…
-You’re rude!

5
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:37,220
Who asks about age these days?

6
00:00:40,670 --> 00:00:41,670
Hey, a boy is staring at me.

7
00:00:42,090 --> 00:00:43,900
Am I so pretty?

8
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:45,900
-I sure am.
-Maybe you’re not Gen Z like me.

9
00:00:46,670 --> 00:00:48,900
Being a Gen Z is like riding the MRT.

10
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,560
Fast and rushed.

11
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:52,900
We love competition.

12
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:55,900
We dare to be different.

13
00:00:57,240 --> 00:00:58,560
But we all...

14
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,240
have our own goals.

15
00:01:03,780 --> 00:01:06,210
Just like me, who wants to chase my dream.

16
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,400
I want to quickly make it happen.

17
00:01:08,770 --> 00:01:10,280
Because I know that

18
00:01:11,410 --> 00:01:13,330
Gen Alpha will catch up to me soon!

19
00:01:16,430 --> 00:01:17,480
So I have to run.

20
00:01:17,480 --> 00:01:18,070
Run.

21
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:18,900
Run.

22
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:19,770
Run.

23
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:21,640
Be hurry and fight for it,

24
00:01:22,230 --> 00:01:23,680
or else my dream is—

25
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:31,820
Sorry, I wasn’t looking.

26
00:01:31,820 --> 00:01:32,820
I’m really sorry.

27
00:01:33,530 --> 00:01:34,370
It’s okay.

28
00:01:34,370 --> 00:01:35,490
I wasn’t paying attention.

29
00:01:36,520 --> 00:01:37,080
Well,

30
00:01:37,650 --> 00:01:40,090
are you auditioning for Ultimate Wolf too?

31
00:01:40,990 --> 00:01:41,520
Mhm.

32
00:01:43,250 --> 00:01:44,330
Good luck.

33
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:46,820
I’ve auditioned for many agencies,

34
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,970
but I still haven’t passed.

35
00:01:50,039 --> 00:01:51,240
Nice to meet you.

36
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:53,479
I hope we get to meet again at the agency.

37
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,470
Then I’ll go audition first.

38
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:19,460
This is the part

39
00:03:19,460 --> 00:03:20,329
that…

40
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:23,290
I believe many people will be shocked.

41
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:25,610
Who are you?

42
00:03:25,610 --> 00:03:26,190
Ahh.

43
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:28,460
P’Gun, you don’t know me?

44
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:29,050
Who?

45
00:03:30,510 --> 00:03:32,010
What’s your name?

46
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:33,110
I’m Jeng.

47
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:35,220
Do you know me?

48
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,140
Oh.

49
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,060
Just like that.

50
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:41,870
You know, actually,

51
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,630
I picked you because you’re

52
00:03:44,630 --> 00:03:46,430
the worst, useless and hopeless one.

53
00:03:46,430 --> 00:03:47,890
Your singing is terrible.

54
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:50,530
Do you know my songs?

55
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:51,660
What songs?

56
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:53,400
“Born to be cool.”

57
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:56,040
“Watch your mouth, kiddo.”

58
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:58,120
“Burp and break up.”

59
00:03:58,120 --> 00:04:00,290
“My fresh farts.”

60
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:01,340
Seriously?

61
00:04:01,730 --> 00:04:02,720
Those are your songs?

62
00:04:02,850 --> 00:04:03,360
Yes.

63
00:04:03,770 --> 00:04:04,850
And my last song is…

64
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:09,020
“Biggg egooo.”

65
00:04:09,130 --> 00:04:10,730
996

66
00:04:10,730 --> 00:04:12,280
997

67
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,780
998

68
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:15,310
999!

69
00:04:16,370 --> 00:04:17,160
Hey.

70
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:19,410
Why is the website spinning like this?

71
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:21,079
My fingers are locking up.

72
00:04:22,150 --> 00:04:23,390
Already?

73
00:04:24,250 --> 00:04:25,360
Look at Pier.

74
00:04:29,250 --> 00:04:30,590
Don’t be baffled.

75
00:04:31,330 --> 00:04:32,950
It’s already been 72 hours,

76
00:04:33,210 --> 00:04:34,780
and we haven’t reached 1,000 views.

77
00:04:35,210 --> 00:04:36,490
How could we be idols?

78
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,780
I think…

79
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,560
I’m going to report this to YouTube.

80
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:45,090
Because no matter what,

81
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:46,560
T-Pop stage,

82
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,190
Whoa.

83
00:04:47,190 --> 00:04:48,590
Thai Music Countdown,

84
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:49,780
CAT Festival,

85
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:50,780
Ooh.

86
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:51,570
Pa Ted.

87
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:52,950
Big Mountain Festival

88
00:04:52,950 --> 00:04:54,960
are waiting for me!

89
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:56,490
That’s more like it.

90
00:04:56,490 --> 00:04:57,740
Let’s keep going!

91
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:04,740
(Praying)

92
00:05:05,650 --> 00:05:06,430
Please go up.

93
00:05:06,430 --> 00:05:09,650
With all the good deeds I’ve done,

94
00:05:09,650 --> 00:05:11,280
please don’t let me fail.

95
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:18,260
I’ve made my decision.

96
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:21,400
-I’m disbanding—
-Wait!

97
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:23,160
-I’m disbanding—
-Wait!

98
00:05:23,370 --> 00:05:24,960
Please don’t!

99
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,740
I haven’t bought a house for my mom yet.

100
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:28,510
I don’t even have a car.

101
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:29,990
How would you?

102
00:05:30,970 --> 00:05:32,620
The views are only in the thousands.

103
00:05:32,960 --> 00:05:33,740
But Boss,

104
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:34,740
all of our songs’ views

105
00:05:35,020 --> 00:05:36,490
have exceeded the target.

106
00:05:36,490 --> 00:05:38,320
Because I’ve been streaming with you

107
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,500
in the room next door.

108
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:41,220
Can you see my thumbs?

109
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:43,010
It might be locked for the rest of my life.

110
00:05:46,450 --> 00:05:49,220
Boss, you have such a visionary mindset.

111
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:49,740
True.

112
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:53,510
You’re kind and dress so elegantly.

113
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,380
Elegant my ass.

114
00:05:59,170 --> 00:06:00,370
Even my Gucci pants,

115
00:06:00,370 --> 00:06:02,110
I have to pawn them!

116
00:06:06,910 --> 00:06:07,500
Boss.

117
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:08,880
Well…

118
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,740
We have a song to present.

119
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,160
It’s the song you said

120
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:13,630
it would make us

121
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:16,030
as famous as other T-Pop groups

122
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:17,570
Show me.

123
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,280
Three, two, one.

124
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:23,740
You said I’m like your little brother

125
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:25,850
Can we be lovers already?

126
00:06:25,850 --> 00:06:29,350
I don’t know how to eat properly

127
00:06:29,350 --> 00:06:31,580
I’m obsessed with body hair

128
00:06:31,580 --> 00:06:34,630
Can we grow body hair together?

129
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:38,010
Because I don't want to shave it off

130
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:39,970
Want some body hair, Boss?

131
00:06:41,740 --> 00:06:43,100
That’s kinda gross.

132
00:06:48,870 --> 00:06:50,330
Who said I was going to disband?

133
00:06:50,740 --> 00:06:51,520
I knew it!

134
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,620
He was just joking.

135
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:53,270
But!

136
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:56,740
I…

137
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,470
will give you a new image.

138
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:00,180
Let’s change

139
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:02,740
the target group!

140
00:07:02,990 --> 00:07:04,020
Oh.

141
00:07:04,270 --> 00:07:05,450
You mean…

142
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:08,310
Changing from university students to high school students?

143
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:10,410
Kindergarten, actually.

144
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:11,450
Huh?

145
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:14,140
We’re going to make kids’ songs like Teletubbies,

146
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:16,060
wear mascot costumes, do some Thai dance,

147
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,390
and say…

148
00:07:17,870 --> 00:07:19,470
Juek juek.

149
00:07:19,470 --> 00:07:20,400
But Boss,

150
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,240
that’s unlike idol.

151
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,200
Juek juek.

152
00:07:25,590 --> 00:07:26,740
Juek juek.

153
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:29,110
We’re screwed.

154
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,460
Amen.

155
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:35,870
I hope we get lucky in our new path.

156
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,140
Where are you guys going?

157
00:07:41,550 --> 00:07:42,220
Oh.

158
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,210
I’ve made up my mind.

159
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:46,930
I’m quitting and starting a new life.

160
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:51,530
I’m not doing that.

161
00:07:51,530 --> 00:07:53,170
Singing for kindergarten kids?

162
00:07:53,470 --> 00:07:54,830
That’s not being an idol,

163
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:57,040
more like a kindergarten teacher.

164
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:58,460
You’re right.

165
00:07:58,860 --> 00:07:59,900
I’m done with this too.

166
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:01,360
I think

167
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,260
someone with my look

168
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,700
can walk in front of the GMM building

169
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,700
and get noticed by some big shot.

170
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,450
Or should I just call P’Option?

171
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:14,010
Maybe I’ll become someone like Keng Namping or Zee NuNew.

172
00:08:15,010 --> 00:08:15,700
So…

173
00:08:16,420 --> 00:08:18,130
When are you guys leaving?

174
00:08:19,170 --> 00:08:20,240
Right now.

175
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:22,700
No need to wait or check for an auspicious time.

176
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:23,810
Nothing is tying us down.

177
00:08:23,810 --> 00:08:24,870
Wait.

178
00:08:25,330 --> 00:08:26,590
Did you already tell Boss?

179
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,330
Of course.

180
00:08:28,860 --> 00:08:30,190
While you were sleeping.

181
00:08:30,970 --> 00:08:31,700
But…

182
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,059
Boss was so calm.

183
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,570
Just like when we only had a few hundred views.

184
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,700
We’re not an idol group anymore,

185
00:08:43,549 --> 00:08:45,380
but a real life documentary.

186
00:08:46,610 --> 00:08:47,210
Mhm.

187
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:49,100
I…

188
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:51,460
miss my mom’s cooking more than the views.

189
00:08:52,530 --> 00:08:53,090
Hey.

190
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:54,440
Can I join you?

191
00:08:55,050 --> 00:08:56,160
Since we’re quitting,

192
00:08:56,160 --> 00:08:57,520
I don't wanna be starve.

193
00:08:58,990 --> 00:08:59,700
Then,

194
00:09:00,250 --> 00:09:01,590
I’ll have two fried eggs.

195
00:09:02,070 --> 00:09:04,170
Not fully cooked, just like our group’s future.

196
00:09:04,170 --> 00:09:05,140
Bro.

197
00:09:05,870 --> 00:09:07,040
That's not helping.

198
00:09:07,930 --> 00:09:08,580
Yeah.

199
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:09,700
For me,

200
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:14,230
we’re too old to sing for kindergarten kids.

201
00:09:14,230 --> 00:09:16,820
We can’t keep failing the higher ups anymore.

202
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:19,330
Boss doesn’t see anything in us.

203
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,700
What about me?

204
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,100
Jeng.

205
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:26,590
A leader like you is a rare find.

206
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,340
Most people run away when they face problems.

207
00:09:29,590 --> 00:09:31,520
But I believe one day,

208
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:33,100
you’ll become a great leader.

209
00:09:33,990 --> 00:09:34,700
Keep fighting.

210
00:09:36,490 --> 00:09:38,170
Alright then.

211
00:09:38,490 --> 00:09:40,170
I’ll go tell Boss.

212
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,580
If you guys finish packing,

213
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,490
you can go home first.

214
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:46,460
Catch up with us.

215
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,050
Yeah.

216
00:09:47,050 --> 00:09:47,700
See you.

217
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,420
Good luck. Come after us soon.

218
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:53,700
Let’s go around the GMM building.

219
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:55,540
Tell your mom I’m starving.

220
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:57,700
-Let me walk first.
-I’m hungry.

221
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,100
What should I do?

222
00:10:19,830 --> 00:10:20,390
Boss.

223
00:10:21,130 --> 00:10:21,820
I…

224
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:22,850
Say no more.

225
00:10:25,790 --> 00:10:27,330
You want to quit too, don't you?

226
00:10:29,380 --> 00:10:30,060
Boss.

227
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:32,460
-I mean…
-Don’t call me Boss anymore.

228
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,510
Just call me brother.

229
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:39,700
From now on,

230
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:41,820
I’m no longer your boss.

231
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:45,190
I’m not managing you anymore,

232
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,860
so it’s not right to call me Boss.

233
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:50,110
But…

234
00:10:50,570 --> 00:10:52,100
Can I be your older brother?

235
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,140
I’ll still look after you.

236
00:10:55,790 --> 00:10:56,820
And if you miss me,

237
00:10:57,890 --> 00:10:59,110
we can meet up for a meal.

238
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,530
I’ll treat you,

239
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,850
but we’ll split the bill.

240
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:07,350
Boss, I…

241
00:11:07,350 --> 00:11:08,150
Jeng.

242
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:12,330
You…

243
00:11:16,970 --> 00:11:18,330
You’re a good leader.

244
00:11:19,810 --> 00:11:21,340
You’re much better than you think,

245
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:24,500
my dear little brother.

246
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,490
Don’t blame yourself.

247
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:31,600
Don’t think you’re not good.

248
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:35,350
You’re always good enough for me.

249
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:39,900
I hope you succeed at your new agency.

250
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:42,880
What new agency, Boss?

251
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:46,150
Who said I’m leaving?

252
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:47,700
I’m staying with you.

253
00:11:49,180 --> 00:11:50,460
I’ll fight alongside you.

254
00:11:53,410 --> 00:11:54,700
Jeng!

255
00:11:59,660 --> 00:12:02,470
I thought you were going to leave me too.

256
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:03,970
Boss.

257
00:12:04,410 --> 00:12:06,050
I’m completely soaked.

258
00:12:06,930 --> 00:12:07,500
But…

259
00:12:09,450 --> 00:12:10,860
I have a proposal.

260
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:12,190
What is it?

261
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:13,660
If you don’t quit,

262
00:12:14,050 --> 00:12:15,100
I’ll listen to anything.

263
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:16,240
Well…

264
00:12:17,190 --> 00:12:19,040
Please let me choose the new members.

265
00:12:19,950 --> 00:12:20,890
If it doesn’t work out,

266
00:12:21,460 --> 00:12:23,550
I’ll do anything you say.

267
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:24,430
Anything?

268
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,250
Except

269
00:12:26,530 --> 00:12:28,660
singing in a mascot costume.

270
00:12:31,390 --> 00:12:32,140
Okay.

271
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:32,770
So…

272
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:35,230
Where are you going to find new members?

273
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:37,060
Your friends all left the group.

274
00:12:37,060 --> 00:12:38,470
I'l try to invite my friends.

275
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:45,090
Alright.

276
00:12:47,020 --> 00:12:49,190
If you trust me, then I trust you.

277
00:12:49,830 --> 00:12:50,430
And…

278
00:12:50,910 --> 00:12:51,930
I have one more request.

279
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,510
What is it?

280
00:12:54,220 --> 00:12:55,220
Don’t tell me…

281
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:56,950
you want a paycheck now.

282
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:57,950
No.

283
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:01,530
I just want to call you

284
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:03,300
Boss, like before.

285
00:13:05,370 --> 00:13:06,660
Because you’re like my father,

286
00:13:07,790 --> 00:13:08,820
my older brother,

287
00:13:10,260 --> 00:13:11,780
and my benefactor.

288
00:13:14,150 --> 00:13:15,100
Without you,

289
00:13:16,310 --> 00:13:17,770
I wouldn’t be who I am today.

290
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:20,910
I love you

291
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,010
and respect you so much.

292
00:13:26,130 --> 00:13:27,510
Jeng.

293
00:13:30,410 --> 00:13:33,350
Boss, I can’t breathe.

294
00:13:34,660 --> 00:13:36,470
I’m not leaving you, okay?

295
00:13:38,660 --> 00:13:39,220
Huh?

296
00:13:39,570 --> 00:13:40,470
You’re a monk?

297
00:13:40,990 --> 00:13:42,540
You…

298
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:43,870
I mean, sir.

299
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:45,400
How many years have it been?

300
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:47,660
Ten years.

301
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:50,010
Ten years?

302
00:13:52,090 --> 00:13:54,660
May you be blessed.

303
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:56,290
I hope

304
00:13:56,290 --> 00:13:58,980
you still remember when we danced to Sorry Sorry

305
00:13:58,980 --> 00:13:59,860
by Super Junior

306
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:01,420
at the Children’s Day event.

307
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:04,080
I’m sorry, sorry, sorry.

308
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:09,010
What should I do?

309
00:14:09,920 --> 00:14:12,050
My first friend already has two kids.

310
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,690
The second one is at the border.

311
00:14:14,180 --> 00:14:15,490
The third one became a monk.

312
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:17,740
And I was so confident talking to Boss.

313
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,340
What now?

314
00:14:25,590 --> 00:14:27,190
How about...

315
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:31,190
Please.

316
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:33,250
If I still have good karma left,

317
00:14:33,620 --> 00:14:35,130
I pray to gods.

318
00:14:35,370 --> 00:14:39,060
Please help me find new members miraculously.

319
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:40,480
Amen.

320
00:14:47,180 --> 00:14:49,090
Six, seven, eight.

321
00:14:49,090 --> 00:14:51,260
Raise your right arm.

322
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:54,530
Six, seven, eight, again.

323
00:14:54,530 --> 00:14:56,060
Go, go.

324
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:59,150
Next, switch sides.

325
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:01,590
Very good.

326
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:03,330
Right, left, right.

327
00:15:03,330 --> 00:15:05,420
So handsome.

328
00:15:05,810 --> 00:15:06,320
Right.

329
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:08,630
Oh my, he’s too good.

330
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:10,550
This isn’t just a regular aerobics class.

331
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,110
He’s the idol of these grandmas!

332
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:15,290
Before we finish, I have a gift for you.

333
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,170
So handsome.

334
00:15:24,170 --> 00:15:25,780
Really handsome.

335
00:15:25,780 --> 00:15:27,830
Help me, I’m about to faint.

336
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:29,420
This is it.

337
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:31,090
My savior.

338
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:33,290
Thank God.

339
00:15:40,340 --> 00:15:42,260
I’ll be going now. Bye.

340
00:15:57,740 --> 00:15:58,740
Is something wrong?

341
00:15:59,590 --> 00:16:02,560
I felt an energy from your dance.

342
00:16:02,910 --> 00:16:04,260
And the world needs it.

343
00:16:05,990 --> 00:16:07,170
What kind of energy?

344
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:08,350
Idol energy.

345
00:16:13,260 --> 00:16:15,470
I guess the gods haven’t worked yet.

346
00:16:19,070 --> 00:16:20,260
What’s your name?

347
00:16:20,260 --> 00:16:21,260
I’m Fong.

348
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:23,910
Do you need something? I have to go.

349
00:16:23,910 --> 00:16:25,420
Hey, wait.

350
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:27,370
What I wanted to say is…

351
00:16:28,050 --> 00:16:28,900
Fong,

352
00:16:29,380 --> 00:16:30,600
please become an idol with me.

353
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:38,640
Damn.

354
00:16:39,050 --> 00:16:40,570
The gods still haven’t helped.

355
00:16:43,430 --> 00:16:44,160
Fine.

356
00:16:44,500 --> 00:16:45,660
Please forget it.

357
00:16:48,870 --> 00:16:49,700
I’m interested.

358
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:57,940
The gods have helped me!

359
00:17:02,930 --> 00:17:04,450
Why are you changing the members?

360
00:17:05,599 --> 00:17:06,180
Well,

361
00:17:06,670 --> 00:17:09,089
everyone in my group quit.

362
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:10,440
Because our Boss

363
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,760
made us sing kindergarten songs

364
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:16,020
and wear mascot costumes on Children’s Day.

365
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:18,460
But our dream

366
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:21,140
is to perform a countdown show at Siam.

367
00:17:25,069 --> 00:17:26,329
Actually,

368
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:28,030
I was going to quit too.

369
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,500
But Boss saw my potential.

370
00:17:33,390 --> 00:17:34,370
I think…

371
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,140
having someone see your worth

372
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,010
is really amazing.

373
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:41,890
That’s why I chose to stay

374
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,680
and try again.

375
00:17:46,930 --> 00:17:48,980
I’ve also lost my dream before.

376
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:50,810
I was chosen.

377
00:17:51,090 --> 00:17:51,650
But…

378
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:53,500
But what?

379
00:17:57,500 --> 00:17:59,070
Damn!

380
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,980
Were you a cover dance champion?

381
00:18:05,110 --> 00:18:05,760
Yes.

382
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,020
But my boss liked P’Add Carabao.

383
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,620
He wanted me to make

384
00:18:12,170 --> 00:18:14,380
Thai folk rock songs.

385
00:18:15,190 --> 00:18:16,380
That's not it!

386
00:18:16,380 --> 00:18:18,930
Why should we let others choose our paths?

387
00:18:18,930 --> 00:18:20,830
What era are we living in?

388
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:23,600
There shouldn’t be any limits

389
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:24,750
or restrictions.

390
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:29,040
Your life

391
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:32,260
can’t be replaced by anyone else.

392
00:18:32,890 --> 00:18:34,220
Being true to yourself

393
00:18:34,890 --> 00:18:35,970
is the best.

394
00:18:37,010 --> 00:18:38,770
I guess no one understands me

395
00:18:38,770 --> 00:18:39,600
as much as you do.

396
00:18:41,140 --> 00:18:42,140
As for me,

397
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:44,370
I have to wear a mascot costume

398
00:18:45,060 --> 00:18:46,780
and sing for kindergarten kids.

399
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:50,320
It seems we’re both hurt.

400
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:52,350
Then let’s start a group together.

401
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:55,390
Deal!

402
00:18:55,650 --> 00:18:56,720
Woohoo!

403
00:19:05,060 --> 00:19:06,240
Excuse me.

404
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:08,250
Would you like to join our group?

405
00:19:08,250 --> 00:19:09,510
There are two of us.

406
00:19:09,930 --> 00:19:12,730
We could be a band.

407
00:19:12,730 --> 00:19:14,840
-One with male and female members.
-No, thanks.

408
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:16,930
Hey.

409
00:19:17,320 --> 00:19:18,240
It’s fine.

410
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:22,310
We need to find more members.

411
00:19:27,060 --> 00:19:28,470
Oh!

412
00:19:29,060 --> 00:19:30,440
I know someone.

413
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,250
Who?

414
00:19:31,520 --> 00:19:32,470
My old friend.

415
00:19:32,910 --> 00:19:34,730
I’ll call him.

416
00:19:34,730 --> 00:19:36,470
Before you call,

417
00:19:36,470 --> 00:19:37,680
check on him first.

418
00:19:38,330 --> 00:19:39,440
Check what?

419
00:19:40,060 --> 00:19:42,360
Check if he’s become a monk.

420
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:45,950
He isn’t religious.

421
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:47,690
Oh.

422
00:19:48,410 --> 00:19:50,290
I’ve seen him going to temples though.

423
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,390
Is he a temple attendant?

424
00:19:54,430 --> 00:19:55,270
Back then,

425
00:19:55,570 --> 00:19:56,750
he was a rapper.

426
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:58,950
His stage name was "CCT Cutter J."

427
00:19:58,950 --> 00:20:00,650
His words were sharp,

428
00:20:00,650 --> 00:20:02,470
sharper than a paper cutter,

429
00:20:02,470 --> 00:20:04,120
and stronger than a poisoned knife.

430
00:20:04,750 --> 00:20:08,250
I know CCT means cutter.

431
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:10,060
But what does J stand for?

432
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:11,330
Jaew.

433
00:20:12,610 --> 00:20:13,710
His mom’s name.

434
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:17,060
He might want to remember his mom while rapping.

435
00:20:17,640 --> 00:20:20,060
So what does he do now?

436
00:20:20,270 --> 00:20:21,490
He changed careers.

437
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,170
To the left, our hero for the day.

438
00:20:27,170 --> 00:20:28,650
Row faster!

439
00:20:28,650 --> 00:20:31,000
The right boat is a bad boy, but it’s okay.

440
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,040
Catch up quickly.

441
00:20:33,040 --> 00:20:37,400
Come on, faster. It'll be too late!

442
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:40,400
Left side, row harder. Right side, row harder.

443
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:44,780
What a very close match. They’re about to win.

444
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:46,000
Oh yeah!

445
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,830
-That was amazing!
-Whoa.

446
00:20:48,470 --> 00:20:50,600
He’s not a normal boat race commentator.

447
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:52,170
He’s clearly a legendary rapper.

448
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:53,320
Should we invite him?

449
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:53,970
Sure.

450
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,200
Give me the map.

451
00:20:56,350 --> 00:20:58,400
Where is he?

452
00:21:01,690 --> 00:21:02,950
Suphan Buri province.

453
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,640
Suphan Buri?

454
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:13,430
We came all this way. We have to meet him.

455
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:15,190
Of course.

456
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:16,310
My back hurts.

457
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:17,440
Ouch.

458
00:21:18,330 --> 00:21:19,070
We’re here.

459
00:21:24,930 --> 00:21:25,560
Hey.

460
00:21:26,350 --> 00:21:27,530
We came all this way.

461
00:21:27,830 --> 00:21:29,800
We better get an amazing rapper.

462
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:33,150
Of course, I’ve already talked to Cutter.

463
00:21:34,410 --> 00:21:36,780
Anyway, why did that guy come with us?

464
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:41,720
I told Boss we're going to find a rapper in another province,

465
00:21:42,290 --> 00:21:43,630
so he sent him with us.

466
00:21:44,090 --> 00:21:44,780
Boss said

467
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:49,240
he’ll be taking care of superstars like us.

468
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,240
Then where are our fans?

469
00:22:00,090 --> 00:22:01,870
Come on.

470
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:02,930
It’s good to be prepared.

471
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:05,280
We’ll be famous soon anyway.

472
00:22:05,990 --> 00:22:09,160
Then, where is the boat race event?

473
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:10,780
Good question.

474
00:22:14,670 --> 00:22:15,640
Let’s ask that lady.

475
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,570
Two Thai teas, please.

476
00:22:24,780 --> 00:22:28,640
Aunt, what time does the long tail boat race start?

477
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:31,120
Oh, it ended an hour ago.

478
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:32,170
Where have you been?

479
00:22:32,170 --> 00:22:33,630
Look over there.

480
00:22:38,510 --> 00:22:39,670
Don’t tell me…

481
00:22:40,430 --> 00:22:42,190
we came here for nothing.

482
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:44,780
Today, we have something special.

483
00:22:44,780 --> 00:22:47,570
Everything looks so delicious.

484
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,970
Come take a look.

485
00:22:50,970 --> 00:22:51,790
Cutter!

486
00:22:51,790 --> 00:22:53,410
That’s his voice! I remember it.

487
00:22:54,290 --> 00:22:55,230
Cutter!

488
00:22:56,920 --> 00:22:59,920
When I say wave, you say call.

489
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:02,450
-Wave.
-Call!

490
00:23:02,450 --> 00:23:04,890
When I say call, you say stop.

491
00:23:04,890 --> 00:23:07,800
-Call.
-Stop!

492
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:08,640
Okay.

493
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,550
Hey, Mommy.

494
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:11,880
Please stop. We’ve got customers.

495
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:12,650
Yo.

496
00:23:13,290 --> 00:23:13,990
Okay.

497
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:26,930
Hey.

498
00:23:29,230 --> 00:23:30,310
Long time no see.

499
00:23:33,410 --> 00:23:35,350
You’ve gotten handsome.

500
00:23:35,350 --> 00:23:36,680
As I should.

501
00:23:38,410 --> 00:23:41,010
Hey yo, what’s up, bro.

502
00:23:41,010 --> 00:23:42,430
Hey, hey, hey!

503
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:44,780
Who’s he?

504
00:23:45,410 --> 00:23:48,410
Well, do you want to form a group with us?

505
00:23:48,410 --> 00:23:50,780
You said you wanted to become an idol.

506
00:23:50,780 --> 00:23:54,780
Now, Ultimate Wolf is reaching out to us.

507
00:23:55,120 --> 00:23:57,560
This guy is a member of the agency.

508
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:58,450
This guy?

509
00:23:59,210 --> 00:23:59,960
This is Jeng?

510
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:03,050
A member?

511
00:24:03,170 --> 00:24:04,780
Alright, listen.

512
00:24:04,780 --> 00:24:06,780
We’ll become the next wolf.

513
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:08,780
I mean, the next superstar.

514
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,250
Ah.

515
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:13,040
You scared me with that wolf part.

516
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,040
Actually,

517
00:24:16,910 --> 00:24:19,470
what you proposed

518
00:24:20,670 --> 00:24:22,160
is pretty interesting.

519
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:23,270
But…

520
00:24:23,790 --> 00:24:26,160
the job I’m doing now

521
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:29,290
is at its peak.

522
00:24:29,290 --> 00:24:30,560
The highest point,

523
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,590
you know what I mean?

524
00:24:32,920 --> 00:24:33,850
Hah.

525
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:36,510
Don’t you want to be a rapper anymore?

526
00:24:36,910 --> 00:24:38,960
You have so much potential.

527
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:40,780
Whoa.

528
00:24:41,440 --> 00:24:42,530
What a sweet tongue.

529
00:24:43,170 --> 00:24:44,110
Actually,

530
00:24:44,780 --> 00:24:47,350
for me…

531
00:24:47,850 --> 00:24:50,120
I’m really interested.

532
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:51,450
But…

533
00:24:53,090 --> 00:24:54,780
my mom

534
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:58,960
doesn’t support it. She said no.

535
00:24:59,910 --> 00:25:00,650
What?

536
00:25:01,190 --> 00:25:02,490
Who said I don’t support you?

537
00:25:02,490 --> 00:25:03,210
Mom.

538
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:03,930
Yeah!

539
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,290
This is…

540
00:25:09,230 --> 00:25:10,990
such a cool mom.

541
00:25:11,670 --> 00:25:13,770
Let’s go, Mom.

542
00:25:13,770 --> 00:25:16,570
I just don’t support his old agency.

543
00:25:16,570 --> 00:25:18,780
They suddenly changed music style,

544
00:25:18,780 --> 00:25:21,670
and made my son lost his direction.

545
00:25:21,670 --> 00:25:22,990
But from now on…

546
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:23,930
Yes, Mom?

547
00:25:23,930 --> 00:25:25,000
Listen.

548
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:25,590
Yeah?

549
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:27,120
If you have a dream, you need passion.

550
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,150
Passion.

551
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:31,370
And when you have passion, you have to go for it.

552
00:25:31,370 --> 00:25:32,190
Okay, let’s go.

553
00:25:32,190 --> 00:25:34,210
-With friends helping you like this…
-My friends.

554
00:25:34,210 --> 00:25:36,780
-You have to do it.
-Just do it!

555
00:25:36,780 --> 00:25:38,190
-Got it?
-Got it, Mom.

556
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:39,290
I believe in you, baby.

557
00:25:39,290 --> 00:25:40,670
Yeah, my mom believes in me.

558
00:25:40,670 --> 00:25:42,470
-Yeah, you can do it.
-I can do it!

559
00:25:42,470 --> 00:25:44,170
My mom say yes.

560
00:25:44,170 --> 00:25:44,920
Okay, say yes?

561
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:45,800
-Yes!
-Yes.

562
00:25:45,800 --> 00:25:47,910
My mom said yes, okay, we can go.

563
00:25:47,910 --> 00:25:49,390
Yes, let’s go.

564
00:25:49,390 --> 00:25:51,750
Yay!

565
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:54,290
Yes, yes, yes!

566
00:25:57,590 --> 00:25:59,450
I really admire you guys.

567
00:25:59,450 --> 00:26:02,230
You successfully chased me and convinced me to join you.

568
00:26:02,230 --> 00:26:05,150
Mom said she wants me to shine.

569
00:26:05,150 --> 00:26:06,960
That’s the spirit.

570
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:07,850
Yeah.

571
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:10,000
If you don’t come with us,

572
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,200
you’ll regret it.

573
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:15,280
What’s that flashing light?

574
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:17,390
Is someone illegally gambling?

575
00:26:17,950 --> 00:26:20,360
There aren’t any clubs around here.

576
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:21,120
Huh?

577
00:26:21,510 --> 00:26:22,600
What are they looking at?

578
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:23,310
I wonder.

579
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:27,440
Ah!

580
00:26:27,870 --> 00:26:30,250
Someone is jumping off a building!

581
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:32,290
I want to die.

582
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,510
Huh? Jumping off a building?

583
00:26:35,120 --> 00:26:37,360
Hurry, let’s go see it.

584
00:26:40,190 --> 00:26:41,800
Don’t do it. Calm down.

585
00:26:42,780 --> 00:26:44,530
Don’t jump.

586
00:26:44,910 --> 00:26:45,710
Whoa.

587
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:50,590
This is my first time seeing it.

588
00:26:50,890 --> 00:26:52,030
I should record this.

589
00:26:54,520 --> 00:26:56,450
Love

590
00:26:56,450 --> 00:26:59,910
I love you with all my heart

591
00:26:59,910 --> 00:27:00,910
Who is that?

592
00:27:01,330 --> 00:27:05,440
The feelings I’ve kept inside

593
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:10,350
Can you hear it, my love?

594
00:27:10,950 --> 00:27:13,190
I want to ask…

595
00:27:13,360 --> 00:27:14,630
What are you doing?

596
00:27:14,910 --> 00:27:16,520
You sang this song five times already.

597
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,490
But it usually works.

598
00:27:19,650 --> 00:27:21,040
Can you sing a song about

599
00:27:21,040 --> 00:27:22,390
parental love?

600
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,010
Sure.

601
00:27:24,670 --> 00:27:25,570
As you wish.

602
00:27:26,910 --> 00:27:29,150
My mother is the greatest—

603
00:27:29,150 --> 00:27:31,080
My mom left me when I was three!

604
00:27:31,910 --> 00:27:32,910
I only had my grandma!

605
00:27:34,190 --> 00:27:35,810
Sob sob.

606
00:27:35,810 --> 00:27:36,920
I can’t take it anymore!

607
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:38,010
Ah!

608
00:27:38,010 --> 00:27:39,280
Don’t jump!

609
00:27:40,470 --> 00:27:41,530
Change the song.

610
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:42,640
Give me a song about grandma.

611
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:44,670
But I don’t know any songs like that.

612
00:27:44,670 --> 00:27:46,160
Then just make a new one.

613
00:27:47,330 --> 00:27:48,070
Okay.

614
00:27:49,670 --> 00:27:53,090
Grandma

615
00:27:53,090 --> 00:27:57,850
Grandma gobbles longans, grandma’s drool goes down

616
00:27:57,850 --> 00:28:02,370
Please walk carefully and be careful not to fall

617
00:28:02,370 --> 00:28:04,270
My grandma loves eating longans.

618
00:28:04,910 --> 00:28:07,470
I always peel them for her.

619
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,400
I miss you, Grandma.

620
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:12,950
Where are you?

621
00:28:13,930 --> 00:28:14,780
Noi.

622
00:28:15,450 --> 00:28:16,780
Come down.

623
00:28:17,650 --> 00:28:20,270
Come peel longans for me again.

624
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:21,290
Grandma.

625
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:23,370
I miss you.

626
00:28:24,890 --> 00:28:25,950
Come down.

627
00:28:25,950 --> 00:28:29,200
I’ll jump right down to you.

628
00:28:30,550 --> 00:28:32,600
Don’t!

629
00:28:34,370 --> 00:28:36,080
Just come down the stairs.

630
00:28:36,270 --> 00:28:37,720
The stairs?

631
00:28:38,970 --> 00:28:41,710
Okay, wait for me.

632
00:28:41,710 --> 00:28:42,600
Amazing!

633
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,110
How did you know they like longans?

634
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:46,780
Good heavens. That’s him.

635
00:28:47,090 --> 00:28:48,550
My main vocal!

636
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:52,430
Can I cover his face

637
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:56,030
and post it on TikTok ?

638
00:28:56,030 --> 00:28:57,650
Can I?

639
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:01,690
Hello.

640
00:29:02,670 --> 00:29:04,200
Whoa, just now…

641
00:29:04,510 --> 00:29:07,160
Your voice gave me goosebumps!

642
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,090
So,

643
00:29:08,350 --> 00:29:10,780
what’s your name, Mr. Golden Voice?

644
00:29:10,780 --> 00:29:11,640
I’m Yu.

645
00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:15,210
Your voice and your song

646
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:18,780
are so moving

647
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:21,470
that even the Grim Reaper let the man go.

648
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,770
Just because of longans?

649
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:25,890
Well…

650
00:29:26,780 --> 00:29:27,840
It’s art.

651
00:29:28,330 --> 00:29:29,480
It’s symbolism.

652
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,880
Because art isn’t a direct thing.

653
00:29:32,590 --> 00:29:34,990
It’s about...

654
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:39,230
seeing beauty from different perspectives.

655
00:29:39,230 --> 00:29:39,990
Exactly.

656
00:29:41,170 --> 00:29:45,080
It’s like how we can’t see a soul with bare eyes,

657
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:48,410
but we have to use...

658
00:29:48,410 --> 00:29:51,410
our heart to guide our body.

659
00:29:52,630 --> 00:29:55,030
Yes, that’s what I’m looking for.

660
00:29:56,630 --> 00:29:59,440
A poem can’t become great because of a paintbrush.

661
00:29:59,990 --> 00:30:01,390
It becomes great because of

662
00:30:01,750 --> 00:30:02,910
the meaning.

663
00:30:05,430 --> 00:30:06,650
Would you like to join my group?

664
00:30:07,670 --> 00:30:09,430
When Liu Bei met Zhuge Liang,

665
00:30:09,750 --> 00:30:11,040
the land united.

666
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:12,990
You’re the one I’m looking for.

667
00:30:12,990 --> 00:30:14,630
Even more than Liu Bei and Zhuge Liang.

668
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:17,450
Please be my main vocal.

669
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:19,690
Sure.

670
00:30:25,470 --> 00:30:26,480
An aerobics dancer,

671
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:28,600
a boat race commentator,

672
00:30:29,430 --> 00:30:30,630
a rescue volunteer,

673
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:32,230
and…

674
00:30:33,350 --> 00:30:35,170
the last remaining member of the group.

675
00:30:36,350 --> 00:30:37,680
Why does our profile

676
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,470
seem like a bunch of weirdos?

677
00:30:39,470 --> 00:30:41,680
Hahaha.

678
00:30:43,330 --> 00:30:44,080
Uh.

679
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:44,780
Oh.

680
00:30:44,780 --> 00:30:47,950
I’m going to find Sommai.

681
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:49,570
He must be hungry.

682
00:30:49,570 --> 00:30:50,780
Bye.

683
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:57,330
Go practice.

684
00:30:57,330 --> 00:30:58,550
If you do well,

685
00:30:58,780 --> 00:31:00,570
we can sign the contract right away.

686
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:02,780
What if we don’t, Boss?

687
00:31:02,780 --> 00:31:03,750
Do you want to know?

688
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:06,650
We won’t disappoint you.

689
00:31:07,370 --> 00:31:08,160
We won’t.

690
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:12,780
The girl group trainee from our rival agency

691
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:16,600
is about to debut.

692
00:31:16,600 --> 00:31:17,950
Try researching them.

693
00:31:18,510 --> 00:31:19,770
Kamikeme Entertainment!

694
00:31:19,970 --> 00:31:22,050
Yes, Kamikeme.

695
00:31:23,080 --> 00:31:25,590
Every song they released became a hit.

696
00:31:25,590 --> 00:31:26,960
Their views always skyrocket.

697
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,490
Their concert tickets always sold out.

698
00:31:28,490 --> 00:31:31,290
People lined up to buy tickets the moment the mall opened.

699
00:31:31,290 --> 00:31:33,630
People buy tickets online these days, Boss.

700
00:31:33,950 --> 00:31:34,990
That’s it.

701
00:31:36,780 --> 00:31:38,250
How could a music label like that…

702
00:31:38,990 --> 00:31:40,910
be more popular than us?

703
00:31:42,110 --> 00:31:43,600
But they already are!

704
00:31:44,930 --> 00:31:46,040
What did you say, Boss?

705
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,470
Never mind.

706
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:49,770
Guys,

707
00:31:50,780 --> 00:31:51,910
practice hard.

708
00:31:52,890 --> 00:31:54,780
We have to beat them

709
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,510
and shake up the T-Pop industry.

710
00:31:58,510 --> 00:32:00,470
Alright, you may leave.

711
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:02,000
Somjai.

712
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,270
Take them to the practice room.

713
00:32:03,270 --> 00:32:04,550
Sommai at your service.

714
00:32:05,560 --> 00:32:06,650
Yes, that's what I mean.

715
00:32:07,590 --> 00:32:09,000
Go, do your best.

716
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:10,430
Yes, sir.

717
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:13,530
Follow me this way.

718
00:32:13,530 --> 00:32:16,280
Come on, right this way.

719
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:19,000
This way, rookies.

720
00:32:20,030 --> 00:32:21,290
Come here.

721
00:32:22,360 --> 00:32:23,190
Sean.

722
00:32:24,090 --> 00:32:25,010
Yes, sir.

723
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:29,250
How is the investigation about Bai Liu going?

724
00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:30,890
What are they doing?

725
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,360
So this is what happened…

726
00:32:35,730 --> 00:32:36,780
I’m so excited.

727
00:32:36,780 --> 00:32:38,320
We can’t fail this mission.

728
00:32:38,780 --> 00:32:40,530
-Don’t say that.
-Or else we’ll be fired.

729
00:32:40,530 --> 00:32:42,010
What if we run into P'Waii?

730
00:32:42,780 --> 00:32:44,510
Our agency is in crisis.

731
00:32:45,450 --> 00:32:46,780
And what’s with that outfit?

732
00:32:46,780 --> 00:32:47,810
P’Waii.

733
00:32:48,080 --> 00:32:49,130
P’Waii!

734
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:51,090
It’s P’Waii in the flesh.

735
00:32:52,490 --> 00:32:56,110
I can’t stop falling in love

736
00:32:58,150 --> 00:33:01,920
You’re the love I lost

737
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:06,910
Let’s stay apart, so you can love someone else

738
00:33:06,910 --> 00:33:08,650
Oh my god.

739
00:33:09,150 --> 00:33:11,400
No freaking way. I'm so delighted.

740
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,240
Someone still remembers my song.

741
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,650
I’m so happy too.

742
00:33:14,650 --> 00:33:16,110
I’ve been your fan

743
00:33:16,110 --> 00:33:18,600
since you were singing in front of the market.

744
00:33:18,600 --> 00:33:21,400
I even twerked in front of you, remember?

745
00:33:23,970 --> 00:33:25,790
Huh? You don’t?

746
00:33:27,170 --> 00:33:28,090
Yes, sir.

747
00:33:28,090 --> 00:33:31,050
I’m in front of Bai Liu’s company.

748
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:33,680
Somjai followed some celebrities.

749
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,370
I’ve tried to call him back, but he won’t listen.

750
00:33:35,370 --> 00:33:36,530
Very unprofessional.

751
00:33:42,490 --> 00:33:44,350
Sir, I’ll call you back.

752
00:33:44,350 --> 00:33:45,770
There are so many people here.

753
00:34:01,190 --> 00:34:02,210
Jarassi.

754
00:34:03,170 --> 00:34:06,610
Follow up on Lisa’s concert deal at the end of this year.

755
00:34:06,610 --> 00:34:09,760
I’ll make it grand,

756
00:34:09,760 --> 00:34:11,850
bigger than anything we’ve ever done.

757
00:34:12,670 --> 00:34:15,370
Good. Make it so good that

758
00:34:15,870 --> 00:34:17,670
our rival collapses completely.

759
00:34:19,730 --> 00:34:21,000
Don’t worry.

760
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,560
I’m good at collapsing.

761
00:34:23,560 --> 00:34:25,350
Because I collapse all the time.

762
00:34:25,610 --> 00:34:26,330
Great.

763
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:36,230
How dare you mock me like that?

764
00:34:36,780 --> 00:34:38,110
Bai Liu!

765
00:34:41,510 --> 00:34:42,389
By the way,

766
00:34:43,630 --> 00:34:45,389
do you have a problem with Bai Liu?

767
00:34:46,489 --> 00:34:49,199
You keep mentioning her.

768
00:34:51,070 --> 00:34:52,630
It’s nothing.

769
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:55,650
Go back to work.

770
00:34:57,430 --> 00:34:58,190
Yes, sir.

771
00:34:58,780 --> 00:35:00,550
I’ll take care of my business.

772
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:18,170
Are you free tonight?

773
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,490
I want to negotiate.

774
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:25,130
I'm so ready, woohoo!

775
00:35:30,270 --> 00:35:31,980
This place is amazing.

776
00:35:33,360 --> 00:35:34,190
This is

777
00:35:35,000 --> 00:35:36,410
our practice room.

778
00:35:36,410 --> 00:35:38,210
Isn't it a warehouse?

779
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:40,470
Come on.

780
00:35:40,470 --> 00:35:42,840
BTS started in an apartment.

781
00:35:43,070 --> 00:35:45,450
Steve Jobs also started in a garage.

782
00:35:45,450 --> 00:35:47,050
And we’re starting here.

783
00:35:48,150 --> 00:35:50,030
At a warehouse?

784
00:35:50,030 --> 00:35:51,230
Yeah.

785
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:54,240
It’s not that bad.

786
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:56,930
But can we really practice here?

787
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,070
Of course.

788
00:35:59,590 --> 00:36:02,110
Our voice sounds good even without mixing.

789
00:36:03,390 --> 00:36:06,450
But I feel some kind of presence here.

790
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,270
I just feel hot.

791
00:36:10,280 --> 00:36:13,740
Why don’t we practice in the room the Boss gave us?

792
00:36:13,740 --> 00:36:14,560
No.

793
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:16,160
If we go there,

794
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:18,240
Sean the spy will report us.

795
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,270
Sir. Sir.

796
00:36:21,370 --> 00:36:24,640
We can’t let him see us before we’re ready.

797
00:36:26,210 --> 00:36:27,350
Good point.

798
00:36:27,870 --> 00:36:29,390
Then should we start now?

799
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:30,440
Okay.

800
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,050
Come.

801
00:36:31,050 --> 00:36:31,740
Come on.

802
00:36:31,740 --> 00:36:32,550
Let’s go.

803
00:36:32,550 --> 00:36:33,310
Go.

804
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:57,250
What should I do?

805
00:36:58,030 --> 00:36:59,490
How am I supposed to apologize?

806
00:37:00,730 --> 00:37:01,610
How about this?

807
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:03,520
Bai Liu!

808
00:37:03,520 --> 00:37:05,740
I’m really sorry.

809
00:37:05,740 --> 00:37:07,590
Please forgive me.

810
00:37:07,590 --> 00:37:09,070
I was wrong.

811
00:37:11,010 --> 00:37:11,920
No.

812
00:37:12,210 --> 00:37:13,600
It looks so dumb.

813
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:14,610
Not cool at all.

814
00:37:15,270 --> 00:37:16,200
Maybe this.

815
00:37:17,390 --> 00:37:19,400
Hey, hello, Bai Liu.

816
00:37:19,890 --> 00:37:22,110
Can you forgive me, please?

817
00:37:22,110 --> 00:37:25,200
I’m sorry, sorry, sorry about this.

818
00:37:25,510 --> 00:37:29,030
Apologies. Apologies. Apologies.

819
00:37:29,030 --> 00:37:30,600
No, not this one.

820
00:37:31,010 --> 00:37:33,050
My English is terrible.

821
00:37:33,050 --> 00:37:34,150
Forget it.

822
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,000
Or maybe.

823
00:37:36,590 --> 00:37:38,680
I should just act cool.

824
00:37:42,570 --> 00:37:43,400
Bai Liu.

825
00:37:43,950 --> 00:37:44,770
I…

826
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:46,810
want to apologize

827
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:48,730
for what I did.

828
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:51,190
I was really wrong.

829
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:52,630
Please,

830
00:37:53,320 --> 00:37:55,240
forgive me, Bai Liu.

831
00:38:00,880 --> 00:38:03,120
Long time no see, Crayons.

832
00:38:04,070 --> 00:38:05,170
Just call me Si Tian.

833
00:38:05,170 --> 00:38:06,120
We’re Thai.

834
00:38:06,790 --> 00:38:09,470
Why can’t I call you the way I used to?

835
00:38:10,190 --> 00:38:12,070
Or should I call you...

836
00:38:13,030 --> 00:38:14,730
candle stick?

837
00:38:17,290 --> 00:38:18,770
Whatever you want.

838
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:24,530
What did you call me here for?

839
00:38:25,130 --> 00:38:26,070
Well…

840
00:38:26,490 --> 00:38:30,610
Need advice because your agency’s shutting down?

841
00:38:33,470 --> 00:38:34,850
Don’t play around.

842
00:38:36,470 --> 00:38:37,630
I came to ask for advice

843
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:40,070
as an old friend.

844
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:41,430
Friend?

845
00:38:42,360 --> 00:38:43,530
What kind of friend?

846
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:46,470
Are you talking about…

847
00:38:47,070 --> 00:38:50,570
the friend you kissed in the bathroom?

848
00:38:52,810 --> 00:38:54,920
That was a long time ago.

849
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:56,680
Why bring it up again?

850
00:38:59,150 --> 00:38:59,850
Let’s…

851
00:39:01,740 --> 00:39:03,130
talk about our business.

852
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:04,590
Our?

853
00:39:05,330 --> 00:39:06,490
You really said “our.”

854
00:39:07,330 --> 00:39:08,490
I think

855
00:39:08,890 --> 00:39:10,490
you have no right to say that.

856
00:39:11,270 --> 00:39:13,090
For the past ten years,

857
00:39:13,090 --> 00:39:14,430
what have you done to me?

858
00:39:14,870 --> 00:39:16,670
Do you even remember?

859
00:39:17,490 --> 00:39:18,240
Hah.

860
00:39:18,650 --> 00:39:20,030
You said you loved me

861
00:39:20,530 --> 00:39:21,740
and wanted to date me,

862
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:23,970
but you didn’t dare go public.

863
00:39:24,450 --> 00:39:25,250
Pathetic!

864
00:39:28,490 --> 00:39:30,030
Back then,

865
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,550
we were still young.

866
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,740
Same-sex marriage wasn’t legal yet.

867
00:39:36,850 --> 00:39:38,120
Same-sex marriage?

868
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:41,050
That’s just an excuse.

869
00:39:41,610 --> 00:39:42,270
Hey.

870
00:39:42,510 --> 00:39:43,870
Let me tell you something.

871
00:39:45,030 --> 00:39:46,170
